			    STPJS 274</div>
  <p class="cont">unloose,&rdquo;<span class="footRef">1</span> and Christ came according to the words of John, and He was greater than John,<span class="footRef">2</span> because
  He held the keys of the Melchizedek Priesthood<span class="footRef">3</span> and kingdom of God,<span class="footRef">4</span> and had before revealed the
  priesthood of Moses,<span class="footRef">5</span> yet Christ was baptized by John to fulfill all righteousness;<span class="footRef">6</span> and Jesus in His
  teachings says, &ldquo;Upon this rock I will build my Church, and the gates of hell shall not prevail against
  it.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">7</span> What rock? Revelation.</p>
  <p class="std">Again he says, &ldquo;Except a man be born of water and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the
  kingdom of God;&rdquo;<span class="footRef">8</span> and, &ldquo;heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">9</span> If
  a man is born of water and of the Spirit, he can get into the kingdom of God. It is evident the
  kingdom of God was on the earth, and John prepared subjects for the kingdom,<span class="footRef">10</span> by preaching the
  Gospel to them and baptizing them,<span class="footRef">11</span> and he prepared the way before the Savior,<span class="footRef">12</span> or came as a
  forerunner, and prepared subjects for the preaching of Christ;<span class="footRef">13</span> and Christ preached through
  Jerusalem<span class="footRef">14</span> on the same ground where John had preached; and when the apostles were raised up,
  they worked in Jerusalem,<span class="footRef">15</span> and Jesus commanded them to tarry there until they were endowed<span class="footRef">16</span>
  with power from on high.<span class="footRef">17</span> Had they not work to do in Jerusalem? They did work, and prepared a
  people for the Pentecost.<span class="footRef">18</span> The kingdom of God was with them before the day of Pentecost, as well
  as afterwards; and it was also with John, and he preached the same Gospel and baptism that Jesus
  and the apostles preached after him.<span class="footRef">19</span> The endowment was to prepare the disciples for their missions
  unto the world.<span class="footRef">20</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Divine Authority Necessary to Make Ordinances Valid</div>
  <p class="std">Whenever men can find out the will of God and find an administrator legally authorized from
  God, there is the kingdom of God; but where these are not, the kingdom of God is not. All the
  ordinances, systems, and administrations on the earth are of no use to the children of men,<span class="footRef">21</span> unless
  they are ordained and authorized of God;<span class="footRef">22</span> for nothing will save a man but a legal administrator; for
  none others will be acknowledged either by God or angels.<span class="footRef">23</span></p>
  <p class="std">I know what I say; I understand my mission and business.<span class="footRef">24</span> God Almighty is my shield;<span class="footRef">25</span> and
  what can man do if God is my friend?<span class="footRef">26</span> I shall not be sacrificed until my time comes;<span class="footRef">27</span> then I shall
  be offered freely.<span class="footRef">28</span> All flesh is as grass,<span class="footRef">29</span> and a governor</p>
